# =============================================================================
# .dockerignore — Docker BUILD CONTEXT exclusions for the release image builds.
#
# The release-images.yml reusable workflow builds each app image with
# `context: .` (this repo root) via docker/build-push-action. Everything NOT
# excluded here is uploaded into the build daemon's context and is readable by
# any Dockerfile `RUN` step. This file keeps secrets-y and irrelevant paths OUT
# of that context (Story 38.19 supply-chain hardening), so even a malicious
# Dockerfile cannot read e.g. a persisted git credential or a stray .env from
# the context.
# =============================================================================

# VCS metadata — never belongs in an image, and (defense-in-depth) would carry
# any persisted GITHUB_TOKEN out of .git/config. Checkout already runs with
# persist-credentials:false; excluding .git removes the path entirely.
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.gitmodules

# CI / workflow definitions — not needed to build the apps.
.github

# Secrets / local environment files — must never enter a build context.
.env
.env.*
**/.env
**/.env.*
*.pem
*.key
**/*.pem
**/*.key

# Local dev / editor cruft and build output that bloats the context.
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
.idea
.vscode
node_modules
**/node_modules
target
**/target
dist
**/dist
coverage
**/coverage

# Docker / compose files are not build inputs for the app images.
docker-compose*.yml
**/docker-compose*.yml
